<head>PISSPOT</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>CHAMBER POT</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">便壺</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>VESSEL USED FOR KEEPING URINE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. There was no pissoir in ancient China. The hǔ zǐ 虎子 was a colloquial term for a tiger-shape flask into which to urinate in one's bedroom.</p>
<p>NB: Terms like mǎtǒng 馬桶 and mǎzǐ 馬子 as well as biànhú 便壺 are all late.</p>
        </div>
